The paper discusses a dialogue system that generates responses based on real-world facts, which falls under the category of natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The system also uses machine learning techniques such as retrieval-based and reranking modules, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The system also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE) in its approach.
